   "source": [
    "## Research Question\n",
    "\n",
    "1. Do counties in the United States with higher fast-food restaurant density have higher adult obesity rates?\n",
    "2. Is the strength of this relationship moderated when accounting for median household income, grocery store access, and adult physical inactivity?\n",
    "3. Between fast-food restaurant density, median household income, grocery store access, and adult physical inactivity, which is the strongest predictor for adult obesity rate across counties?"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
