    "\n",
    "Obesity is a major public health concern in the United States, affecting millions of adults and increasing the risks of chronic illnesses such as diabetes, heart disease, and hypertension. R[...]\n",
    "\n",
    "Previous research suggests a relationship between fast-food restaurant density and obesity rates. Studies have shown that individuals living in areas with greater access to fast food are mor[...]\n",
    "\n",
    "The relationship between fast food availability and obesity is also affected by other socioeconomic and lifestyle factors. Lower income communities often have greater fast food availability [....]\n",
    "\n",
    "This project aims to examine whether fast food restaurant density is significantly associated with adult obesity rates across U.S. counties. Using county level data from the USDA Food Enviro[...]"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Hypothesis\n",
    "\n",
    "We predict that there will be a strong positive correlation between fast food restaurant density and adult obesity rates. US counties with more fast food restaurant density will tend to have higher obesity rates.\n",
    "\n",
    "We also predict that adult physical inactivity will be positively correlated with obesity, likely being the strongest single predictor. We expect to see a negative correlation between median household income and obesity, as well as between grocery store access and obesity.\n",
    "\n",
    "If the fast food correlation is heavily warped when introducing these 3 variables, the overall correlation is likely confounded by socioeconomic conditions. Median household income as a variable may suppress or mediate the fast food-obesity relationship, suggesting that poverty, not fast food per se, drives obesity.\n",
    "\n",
    "This prediction is based on previous research suggesting that greater access to fast food increases the likelihood of consuming high calorie, low nutrition foods (Fraser et al 2010). Prior studies have also shown[...]"
   ]
  },
  {
